        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> in half (chop them<span class=\"text-highlight\"> in</span> one bunch for speed!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1604.-step-2.n-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1604.-step-2.n-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1604.-step-2.n-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1604.-step-2.n-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1604.-step-2.n-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>vegetable stock cube </strong>in 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> in a large, wide-based pan</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong>, <strong>soft cheese</strong> and<strong> baby kale</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>\n<p>Cook for 1-2 min or until the <strong>baby kale</strong> is starting to wilt – this is your <strong>creamy sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1604.-step-3.n-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1604.-step-3.n-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1604.-step-3.n-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1604.-step-3.n-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1604.-step-3.n-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> gnocchi</strong> and <strong>chopped Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Cook for 3 min or until the <strong>gnocchi</strong> begins to rise to the top of the pot</p>\n<p>Once done, drain, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy cooking water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1604.-step-4.n-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
